{"type":"message","id":"5e8d2d11","parentId":"275579d9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:09:00.691Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c23nlnm0x8dp_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 020803\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's a pending TIC Experiment to implement\r\n- The next action is to implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step according to the goals is to implement the TIC classifier. Let me look at what exists:\r\n\r\n1. `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` - new doc about the insight\r\n2. `logs/pulse_*.md` files - the pulse logs to test on\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC experiment implementation. The goal is:\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy (>70%)\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants (>60%)\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox. Since I can't actually browse the filesystem, I'll need to work based on what I know exists from the context.\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create the TIC classifier script that can analyze the pulse logs. This aligns with the \"Next Action: TIC Experiment\" priority.\r\n\r\nI'll create a PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier, since the environment seems to be Windows-based (pulse.ps1 exists).\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the critical next step for Phase 1 advancement. The hypothesis is that causal structure IS invariant structure - a compressor finding invariants has discovered causation. Need to implement a classifier that tests this on existing pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier script to analyze pulse logs, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure prediction accuracy against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Testing Compression-Causal Duality Hypothesis\r\n# Success Criteria: >70% invariant/variant accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 5,\r\n    [float]$Lambda = 0.7,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogPattern | Sort-Object Name\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt $Lookback + 2) {\r\n    Write-Error \"Insufficient pulse logs. Need at least $($Lookback + 2) files.\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Pulse logs found: $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Lookback window: $Lookback\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Lambda (significance threshold): $Lambda\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Parse pulse content into structured format\r\nfunction Parse-Pulse {\r\n    param([string]$Path)\r\n    $content = Get-Content $Path -Raw\r\n    # Extract key sections via regex\r\n    $goals = [regex]::Matches($content, '## (Active|Pending|Completed).*?(?=##|\\z)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\r\n    $actions = [regex]::Matches($content, '### ACTION\\r?\\n([^\\n]+)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\r\n    $observations = [regex]::Matches($content, '### OBSERVATION\\r?\\n([^\\n]+)', [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::Singleline)\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Path = $Path\r\n        Raw = $content\r\n        Goals = ($goals | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }) -join \" \"\r\n        Actions = ($actions | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }) -join \" | \"\r\n        Observations = ($observations | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value.Trim() }) -join \" | \"\r\n        WordCount = ($content -split '\\s+').Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate n-gram overlap (temporal invariance metric)\r\nfunction Get-NGramOverlap {\r\n    param([string]$Text1, [string]$Text2, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    \r\n    $words1 = ($Text1 -split '\\W+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }).ToLower()\r\n    $words2 = ($Text2 -split '\\W+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }).ToLower()\r\n    \r\n    $ngrams1 = 0..($words1.Count - $N) | ForEach-Object { ($words1[$_..($_+$N-1)] -join ' ') }\r\n    $ngrams2 = 0..($words2.Count - $N) | ForEach-Object { ($words2[$_..($_+$N-1)] -join ' ') }\r\n    \r\n    $overlap = ($ngrams1 | Where-Object { $ngrams2 -contains $_ }).Count\r\n    $total = [Math]::Max($ngrams1.Count, 1)\r\n    \r\n    return $overlap / $total\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Classify content as invariant or variant\r\nfunction Classify-Content {\r\n    param([float]$Overlap, [float]$Threshold)\r\n    return $Overlap -ge $Threshold\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\nfunction Predict-NextPulse {\r\n    param([array]$InvariantFeatures, [string]$CurrentPulse)\r\n    \r\n    # Extract goals/actions that persist across invariant windows\r\n    $predicted_goals = @()\r\n    $predicted_actions = @()\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($feature in $InvariantFeatures) {\r\n        if ($feature.Overlap -ge $Lambda) {\r\n            $predicted_goals += $feature.Goals\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        PredictedGoals = ($predicted_goals | Select-Object -Unique)\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:08:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774332540690}}
{"type":"message","id":"37e49fda","parentId":"5e8d2d11","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:09:22.420Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log got truncated - it shows a partial mutation that was being applied but the file content is cut off. The mutation was about creating a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment script, but it seems the file write operation may have failed or the log got truncated.\n\nThe pulse output shows:\n1. The TIC experiment is identified as the critical next step\n2. A mutation was parsed to create a new TIC experiment file\n3. But then an OutOfMemoryException was thrown when trying to read the pulse log\n\nSo the key issue is the OutOfMemoryException from the main pulse script when trying to read a large log file. The TIC experiment file was likely not written (or partially written) due to this.\n\n\nThe output is actually quite compressed and shows key steps:\n- TIC hypothesis recognized as critical\n- Mutation proposed to create TIC classifier script\n- OutOfMemoryException occurred during the pulse script execution\n- The log file at `pulse_2026-03-24 020803.md` shows a partial/incomplete TIC experiment file\n\nSo the main issue is: the pulse script tried to write the TIC experiment file but hit an OutOfMemoryException during the broader log reading operation, and the resulting log file shows a truncated version of what was supposed to be created. The file got truncated at 3029 characters, so the mutation likely didn't complete—the OutOfMemoryException during log reading probably prevented the file write from finishing. I should report that the TIC experiment was identified but the pulse script encountered memory issues before it could fully execute.","thinkingSignature":"a55e3f527a245fc0b69667817a2055451c2f7a9a0a8c40f3c688ebf03878c627"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 02:08 AM**\n\n**✅ Completed:**\n- TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment identified as the critical Phase 1 advancement path\n- Hypothesis: **causal structure = invariant structure** — a compressor discovering invariants has effectively discovered causation\n- Mutation parsed to create a TIC classifier script (3029 chars)\n\n**❌ Failed:**\n- `OutOfMemoryException` during `Get-Content -Raw` on a large log file — the pulse script choked trying to read a bloated pulse log before it could write the TIC experiment file\n- The mutation was parsed but likely **not written** to disk (log file itself appears truncated)\n\n**🔧 Recommended Fix:**\nThe large log file (`pulse_2026-03-24 020803.md` itself at ~3KB? Or another log it references?) is causing OOM in `Get-Content -Raw`. Need to either:\n1. Stream-read logs line-by-line instead of `-Raw` in `pulse.ps1`\n2. Purge or archive old pulse logs to reduce memory pressure\n\n**Next pulse** should retry the TIC experiment creation once the OOM issue is resolved. Want me to fix the memory issue in `pulse.ps1` now?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2328,"output":583,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14865,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774332540692}}
